<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-15T17:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-15T17:48:00-05:00" n="759" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul in Chargé of the Legation in
                                Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-15T17:00:00-05:48"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                        1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 17—12:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>8. Hondurean Government reports that rumored revolutionary attempt from
                            Nicaragua has failed completely. The Nicaraguan President has denied all
                            connection therewith, acknowledging legality Hondurean elections and is
                            apprehending Honduras revolutionists.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>